# Roadmap quick edits

When editing the roadmap (add or update tasks only):

- **New task:** Add at the **end** of the Planned list. Use the **next sequential
  number** (e.g. if last task is 14, new task is ### 15.). Title must end with
  `[FE]`, `[BE]`, or `[FE+BE]`. First line of the task body must be `**N sp.**`
  (rough estimate, 1–5) then the goal or first sentence. Do not reorder.
- **Mark task complete:** Append ` — DONE` to that task's title. Do not remove
  it; removal happens during roadmap maintenance.
- **Updating an existing task:** Change goal/tasks/SP as needed; keep the title
  label and SP format. If scope changes, update [FE]/[BE]/[FE+BE].
- **Do not:** Reorder the list, remove DONE items, or run the full maintenance
  workflow. For that, use the roadmap-maintenance skill.
